The evidence with the title 'Mitt Romney on Families & Children ' says 1996: Staff searched full-time to find runaway teenage girl. One day in july 1996, Romney's partner Bob Gay sent an urgent message. Gay's 14-year-old daughter, Melissa, was missing. Romney went into high gear. He shut down the Boston office and sent fifty-six employees to New York City to help find Melissa. The quest  ... 
